  <p class="e"> People Ususlly Meet Their Short Term Goals With Savings. </p><br><br>
  <p class="e">Money is savings account of a bank earna small amount of interest and it's easy to withdraw it whenever neened. People can save in savings back account abd post office     savings accounts etc.</p>

  <h3 class="t">2. What are Investments: </h3>
  <div class="e">Investment is the act of deployment of money out of savings into financial or non - financial products with the expectation of earning higher returns over a period of time. for     e.g. financial products viz. fixed deposit in bank, buying shares in stock market, Investing in mutual funds etc. and non financials products viz. purchase of land, gold, silver, etc. The period     for investments can be for shorts, medium or long-term. It is normal for returns on investments to rise or fall over times.</div>
